# 📐 TeachClear

> An AI-powered Telegram bot that helps Grade 6 Mathematics teachers in Indian classrooms — grounded in the NCERT textbook Ganita Prakash (2024 edition).

---

## 🎯 What is TeachClear?

TeachClear is a teaching support tool, not a student homework solver. It is designed for **teachers** who want practical, curriculum-aligned guidance on how to teach a topic — including concept explanations, step-by-step classroom approaches, low-resource activities, common student misconceptions, and actionable tips.

Every response is grounded in the actual textbook content. TeachClear will not answer from general knowledge — if the topic is not in the selected chapter, it says so.

---

## ✨ Features

- 🌐 **Multilingual** — supports Tamil, Hindi, Telugu, and Kannada
- 📚 **Chapter selection** — teachers pick a chapter from an inline menu; responses are grounded in that chapter's textbook content
- 🔀 **Switch chapters anytime** — use `/chapter` without restarting
- 📖 **Structured responses** — every answer follows a consistent 5-section format
- ✅ **Curriculum-aligned** — built on Ganita Prakash, NCERT Grade 6 Maths (2024)
- 🚫 **Anti-hallucination** — Gemini is explicitly instructed not to answer outside provided textbook context

---

## 📋 Response Format

Every TeachClear response follows this structure:

| Section | What it contains |
|---|---|
| 📖 Concept Overview | 3–5 sentences explaining the concept as it appears in the textbook |
| 🪜 Step-by-Step Teaching | Numbered steps a teacher can follow in class |
| 🎯 Classroom Activity | One low-resource or no-resource activity |
| ⚠️ Common Misconceptions | Typical student errors and how to address them |
| 💡 Teacher Tips | Practical advice on pacing, differentiation, and real-life connections |

---

## 📚 Supported Chapters

TeachClear covers all 10 chapters of Ganita Prakash (NCERT Grade 6, 2024):

| # | Chapter |
|---|---------|
| 1 | Patterns in Mathematics |
| 2 | Lines and Angles |
| 3 | Number Play |
| 4 | Data Handling and Presentation |
| 5 | Prime Time |
| 6 | Perimeter and Area |
| 7 | Fractions |
| 8 | Playing with Constructions |
| 9 | Symmetry |
| 10 | The Other Side of Zero |

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| 🤖 Bot framework | [pyTelegramBotAPI](https://github.com/eternnoir/pyTelegramBotAPI) |
| 🧠 LLM | Google Gemini (`gemini-2.0-flash`) via `google-genai` |
| 🔍 RAG | Prompt-based — keyword scoring over `.txt` chapter files |
| 🐍 Language | Python 3.10+ |

---

## 🗂️ Project Structure

```
teachclear/
│
├── TeachClear.py          # Bot entry point — Telegram handlers, session state, formatting
├── rag.py                 # Retrieves relevant textbook content for a query
├── prompts.py             # Builds the Gemini prompt for each teacher query
├── metadata.py            # Chapter metadata, keywords, and UI strings in all 5 languages
│
├── textbook_chunks/       # One .txt file per chapter (chapter_1.txt … chapter_10.txt)
│   ├── chapter_1.txt
│   ├── chapter_2.txt
│   └── ...
│
├── requirements.txt
├── .env                   # API keys — never committed (see .gitignore)
├── .env.example           # Template for setting up your own .env
└── .gitignore
```

---

## 🚀 Setup

### 1️⃣ Clone the repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/teachclear.git
cd teachclear
```

### 2️⃣ Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3️⃣ Set up environment variables

Copy the example file and fill in your keys:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Your `.env` should contain:

```
TELEGRAM_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash
```

- 🤖 Get your Telegram token from [@BotFather](https://t.me/BotFather)
- 🔑 Get your Gemini API key from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey)

### 4️⃣ Add textbook chapters

Place your chapter text files in `textbook_chunks/`, named exactly:

```
chapter_1.txt
chapter_2.txt
...
chapter_10.txt
```

### 5️⃣ Run the bot

```bash
python TeachClear.py
```

---

## 💬 How to Use

1. 🔍 Open Telegram and search for your bot
2. 👋 Send `/start`
3. 🌐 Pick your language from the inline buttons
4. 📚 Pick a chapter from the list (shown in your chosen language)
5. ✏️ Type your teaching question — TeachClear responds in the language you selected
6. 🔀 Use `/chapter` anytime to switch to a different chapter

---

## 📜 Textbook Attribution

Textbook content is sourced from:

> Ganita Prakash, Grade 6 Mathematics
> National Council of Educational Research and Training (NCERT), 2024 edition (Reprint 2025-26)
> Used for educational, non-commercial purposes.

📖 NCERT textbooks are freely available at [ncert.nic.in](https://ncert.nic.in).

